      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:16:11",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) قَالَ لَا يَجُوزُ فِي الْعَتَاقِ الْأَعْمَى وَ الْمُقْعَدُ وَ يَجُوزُ الْأَشَلُّ وَ الْأَعْرَجُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from his father, from Abu Al Bakhtary, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said that Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘It is not allowed in the emancipations – the blind, and the seated cripple, and it is allowed – the paralysed and the lame’."
        ]
      }
    },
